betterquesting:10.desc:8:
In the year of xxx7, a group known as the Cult of All formed. Their leaders wished to summon the Ancient Ones to cleanse the world of evil.

    However, after their summoning, the Ancient Ones rid the world of more than just the corruption that plagued it. They destroyed and devoured all in their path, good and bad alike. 

    In the end, the Cult of All was successfull, all too well. Entire cities were left empty, the few surviving inhabitants taking to the wilderness to survive. Magic twisted and shifted, monsters and spirits drawn like moths to a flame. 

    However, one group survived, a group known as FOGCraft. They read the warning signs and prepared their greatest spells to hide and protect their small towns of Ferretopia and the neighboring Port Burda. When the cleansing finished and the Ancient Ones departed, FOGCraft began devising The Plan.

    It has been many a year since the cleansing. The twisted magic left by the Ancient Ones lingers, especially in the abandoned and crumbling cities.

    But now the FOGLiner, FOGCraft's greatest invention, is operational. The Plan can now begin...with your help.

Welcome to my Ledger, Engineer. I am the Conductor.
  
    I have been tasked with initiating The Plan with your help. You have many questions, I know...where to begin...

    The FOGLiner is the greatest achievement of technology and magic. It is able to travel by land, sky, and sea, laying and picking up magical tracks as it travels. It can jump between dimensions for short periods of time to avoid danger. It cannot, however, carry much more than a few passengers at a time. Not yet.

    The Plan itself is simple, but executing it is another story. Humanity survives in huddled villages between the decaying Lost Cities of monsters. We have the means, the power, to help. Cleaning out the cities, salvaging what we can, and rebuilding the giant Rail Grid will help jumpstart Civilization once again. For this, we need Engineers like you.

    The FOGLiner has dropped you and others near key points across the world. Areas with villages full of survivors, the underground full of the materials you will need to rebuild, the air full of uncorrupted magic you can use.

    This Ledger will help guide your early steps. How you accomplish The Plan, though, is up to you. Take this Rainbow Rail Ticket to start you off, as well as these Scavenger Tools...

Ah, I forgot the most important of things. With the Ancient One's rampage and subsequent departure, much of the world has been left in decay and destruction. Much of the knowledge once at everyone's fingertips has crumbled away, forgotten to time.

    Fear not, though. FOGCraft scientists and mages have been hard at work. The knowledge, and thus power, is never really gone. It is a bit more difficult to tap into now that cell phones and the internet are in shambles, however.

    You see those Scavenger's Tools I gave you? Well, if you misplaced them, you can make them again, but... try not to lose them?

    Ahem, those Scavenger's Tools are going to be helpful to start out with. Go up to any building in a Lost City and Right Click them on any wall, glass, or other block. See those multicolored smoke puffs? That shows you are Scavenging through the block. There's a good chance the block will crumble with every attempt, so try not to Scavenge straight down, okay? Some of these buildings are very dangerous.

    You see, the buildings of the Lost Cities had technology embedded through and through. Wires, devices, magic crystals. From the Cleansing, much of those decayed and corrupted. The tools allow you to sift through and collect anything useable. Mostly metals, but sometimes...

    Sometimes you can find a Rail Ticket. Orange, in this case. These Tickets formed from the uncorrupted Magic from before the Cleansing. They are the key to unlocking the Forgotten Knowledge.

    Why a Rail Ticket? Well, magic is one part belief, one part cosmic irony, and a whole lot of crazy coincidence. The Rail Ticket is just how we, the Conductor and Engineers of the FOGLiner, see the magic. Or it could just be a loose thematic thing. Either or!

    Show me an Orange Rail Ticket, Engineer!

Life and death are intertwined in magic. The endless dance of birth, life, death, and rebirth. The Red Rail Ticket captures this magic.

    Defeating the various twisted monsters, especially those inhabiting the Lost Cities, will net you Red Rail Tickets.

The draw of the sea, the mysterious creatures under the waves. It is a whole different world with its own magic. Blue Rail Tickets form from the endless shifting of the tide.

    You can find Blue Rail Tickets either by fishing for them, or killing sea creatures such as Guardians or Squids.

The Purple Rail Ticket is one that finds itself in pockets mysteriously. People don't know where they found them, but get the feeling they were meant to be there. Magic works in mysterious ways, as they say.

    Some of the survivors of the Cleansing will trade you a Purple Rail Ticket for helping them. You can also obtain them by helping me in this Ledger, as I have already given you a few!

Holiday meals. A cold soda on a hot day. A hot cocoa on a winter's evening. Your grandmother's special recipe you remember from childhood. Food is the magical key to memories, good or bad, and comfort you on bad days. The Green Rail Ticket shows up when good food is on the menu.

    There are two ways to find the Green Rail Ticket. The easiest, and perhaps slowest, is to forage. Break any tall grass or Gardens from Pam's Harvestcraft you see, not only can you find seeds, you may also find a ticket!

    The other way is a bit more elaborate, but not only will it earn you Green Rail Tickets, but also money! For it, you'll need to construct The Hungry Machine!

    Find me a Green Rail Ticket and I will give you the blueprints to The Hungry Machine, though it isn't necessary. Right Click the Blueprints (or examine the recipe in JEI) to see how to construct it. 

    The blueprints will cycle through the valid blocks. Any Item Input and any Item Outputs from Modular Machinary will work, but I do suggest they are larger than the Tiny versions.

    When you've built The Hungry Machine properly, it will turn green. It is now connected to us back in Ferretopia. Deposit almost any edible item into the Input blocks, and there is a chance you will get a Green Rail Ticket or some Money in return. The more nutritious the item, the better the chance.

    The magic imbued in The Hungry Machine can also be altered by placing Heads, Skulls, MiniHeads, or Statues in the two open spots of the Machine. Placing one in the Left spot (above the controller) will give you Luck, while the Right spot will magically speed up The Hungry Machine a bit.

Money, wealth, and treasure have their own form of magic. Dragons horde it, pirates steal it, and hunters seek it. This magic forms these shiny Yellow Rail Tickets in bank vaults and wallets all over the world.

    Villagers and other inhabitants will gladly sell you Yellow Rail Tickets. They also tend to carry them in their wallets.

Nature itself is magical. Predator and prey. Wild and domestic. Big and small. The cycle of nature is how the White Rail Ticket is formed

    Normal animals, from wild wolves to farm cows, have a chance of dropping a White Rail Ticket when killed.

Magic comes in all forms, from all sources. Lady Luck is perhaps the biggest, and most difficult, form of Magic to manipulate and break even. This is why the Rainbow Rail Ticket only comes about from a roll of the dice, a luck of the draw, and other such random blessings.

    Rainbow Rail Tickets can be found as dungeon loot, very rarely sold in shops, and a few other special places.

Striking the perfect vein of ore, with very little corruption or low quality material, is magic in of itself. Sure, some of the technology we can use makes finding these easier, the perfect strike is still a bit of magic and luck, which is where the Black Rail Ticket comes in.

    Most underground resources that break apart, like Redstone or Lapis Lazuli, can conjure up a Black Rail Ticket for you if you are lucky.

The basics of Furcraftian civilization are second nature to many of us. From basic Swords and Pickaxes to advanced Brewing Stands and Beacons, vanilla Minecraft is in the blood of everything in some way.

    An Iron Sword is a good, basic test of Smelting items in a Furnace and crafting yourself a weapon to protect yourself.

The Lost Cities can get pretty tall, and sometimes the lower levels are in bad disarray. As well, the Cleansing upheaved parts of the landscape into sheer cliffs, so some sort of travel tool is good! Advanced Hook Launchers have a few options for you.

    The Web Hook Launcher, for example, is great for this. With the Launcher and some spare Web Hooks, you can fire off a hook by Left Clicking. When it connects to a surface, hold Right Click to reel yourself in, or Left Click to reel more line out. To disconnect the Hook, hit Q (drop item) on your keyboard!

    In fact, make a Web Hook Launcher for me to show it off!

Building rail stations and housing can be a daunting task by hand. Especially when you get to large sizes, or think outside of classic cubic Furcraftian format. 

    The Builder Guide can definitely help! It has a range of modules you can insert into the Marker, then use the appropriate Mallet on it to expand and contract the ghostly block guide.

    Make a Marker, it'll help you out later.

Sometimes you have a small house, bunker, or other construction you'd really like to move. Moving it by hand can be troublesome... but the engineers over at Port Burda have developed miniaturization technology.

    Place the Capture Base under the center of the structure you wish to miniaturize. Then hold an Empty Capsule and the area it'll capture will be highlighted. If everything you want is in the area, hold and Right Click with the Empty Capsule to activate it. Then Right Click again to throw it and Capture the area!

    Make an Empty Capsule for yourself. Oh, also, living things can't be captured, before you even think about it.

The natural state of materials can be wonderful for construction... but you can do so much more with them. Like Chisel designs into them!

    The Chisel is your tool for the job. Lots of different materials can be carved up... or carved back to normal, thanks to Ferretopia technology of "That didn't happen, shh". Just Right Click with the Chisel to see the interface where you can toss different materials in and see what you can make. Planks, Cobblestone, Marble, and more!

    Make a Chisel and I'll give you something pretty.

Since the Cleansing, the world has become a very dangerous place. Some God blessed Furcraftia with resurrection, but we leave our belongings behind...usually. We have Magic to take up the slack!

    When you die, your stuff will magically be encased in a Grave, and you will rise again holding a Grave Key, marked with the location of your death. Right Click the Key on the Grave and your belongings will return to you. You'll even be wearing your armor again! Well, if it survived your death.

    Life and Death are interconnected in some ways. Killing Zombies can net you some Grave's Dust, which can be used to make special items later on.

Sometimes when building, a full cube of material just isn't necessary. And many times, a material doesn't have an easy way of making Slabs...or does it?

    Using a Saw, you can turn most any material into thin slabs, or other shapes! Just place the material in a Crafting Table, and a Saw above it in the crafting grid. Slice down slabs further and further this way, or combine them back into the main material.

    A Stone Saw is cheap and goes a long way!

The magic from the Cleansing corrupted in strange ways, and not all of them bad! Seemingly random toys and objects became magical, living things. You can't make them, but you may just get lucky enough to find them in the Lost Cities or some Dungeons!

    We call them Inventory Pets. Each one does something different, and almost all of them eat a specific item to recharge. One example is a Coal Nugget.

    Coal Nuggets are good as well for small batches of Smelting, so you don't waste an entire Coal piece.

By now you've probably faced one of the many monstrosities drawn to the Lost Cities and the various villages of survivors. Sometimes, they have collected shiny objects or interesting things in their travels, and that pops out in a convenient Loot Bag for you to open at your leisure!

    Expect to collect many of these things, the monsters have collected a lot of shiny things. The Loot Opener can automatically open and store the loot for you!

Fighting for survival is all well and good, but sometimes you just need something to smile about, to reminisce about the world before the Cleansing.

    Some intrepid citizens have taken up making figurines, for example! MiniHeads have a lot of different collectable figures you can find. They find their way into strange places, like Dungeons, or you can find a Figure Shop in a village!

    Found a nice collectable? A Display Case can show it off for you!

While much of the outside world relies on more direct bartering, Fetteropi and Port Burda have kept a basic economy going. Since we've begun The Plan, merchants and traders have left and set up shop in various villages, helping Engineers along the way.

    Your main source of paper currency will either be fighting monsters or trading with merchants. Some villagers may have ways for you to earn currency as well at some point.

    Some villages have a Bank in which you can access an ATM, where you can deposit your money to a Credit Card so it does not take much room. This, of course, means you'll need a Credit Card in the first place! I'll give you one to start off with, but only if you show me a Fiver...

Bringing technology back to the world and rebuilding it is a daunting task, especially when we need to connect one of our Engineer's remotely. 

    Modular Machinery is just that tool, enabling an Engineer on the field to put together a few basic machine block components, and have it all interface together and with Ferretopia.

    The Hungry Machine is an excellent example of this! Modular Machine blocks in that configuration connect to our food pantries, letting you deposit food directly for us to redistribute to troubled villages later.

    Make a Machine Casing and I'll give you some Modularium in return, helpful to make more machines when we have them ready!

There's not much needed in the realm of roof technology, you know? But hey, improving on things is always good, and Not Enough Roofs helps with that.

    Using materials like Terracotta and Slate, along with a variety of choices for edging, makes buildings look just a little bit nicer, and that's always a good thing in this wrecked world.

    Terracotta... make some of those bricks and I'll give you some Slate Bricks in return, since it might not be plentiful where you are.

It's not always the big, flashy things that improve life the best, but the small things that all combine together.

    Quark is one of those things. Little changes to our daily items to make them more useful, more friendly, and more interesting.

    Like glass shards, breaking 'regular' glass no longer makes it useless, but breaks it into Glass Shards that you can put back together! (Never thought I'd be happy about broken glass...)

    Other useful glass stuff? What about Glass Item Frames? Make one, it's super useful to show off items without anything else in the way. I'll give you another useful thing : Paper Walls! They are very neat for decroating with.

Port Burda arboriculturists (thats tree researcher, kinda?) have developed a fantastically pretty tree called the Rainbow Oak Tree. They've been spreading saplings around for a while before The Plan went into action, so you should be able to find them around.

    But if you want, bring me 5 Oak Saplings and I'll give you a Rainbow one.

The Cleansing left the world in taters and ruins, and the magic ran amok, filling the abandoned cities with monsters and other dangers. Working on your own to enact The Plan, you are no doubt going to need a lot of specific materials, as well as locate special creatures, animals, and more. 

    Ferretopia researchers have come up with this Scanner utility. Insert a module into it, and it can scan the surrounding area and highlight the objects or creatures for you.

    This Scanner must be charged with RF Energy, but you may not have that technology yet. Tell you what, make a Scanner and I'll charge it for you.

   And by charge it, I'll just swap it with a fully charged one, so don't put a module into it yet.

One of the many magical elements that ran amok during the Cleansing was Chaos energy. It warped the land and crystalized underground, as well as empowered a wide variety of gemstones. Gemstones and Chaos energy that you can utilize!

    Port Burda inventor Silent created the Silent's Gems system, working and researching for over a year. Their findings and inventions have created a very modular, versatile system that can create Weapons, Armor, Tools, Accessories, and various useful blocks.

    You'll have to read their research papers in the Quick Start guide I'll hand you, but for now one of the things you can easily make is a Torch Bandolier, using any Silent's Gem. It will automatically place torches around you as necessary.

    I'll give you, in return for making that, an Enchantment Token, which you can use later on by combining it with a Silent's weapon or tool of your choice.

The destruction of the world has filled the rivers with a lot of junk and trash. It can be difficult to  fish up what you want, not to mention it being dreadfully boreing after a while.

    Water Strainers help alleviate this and allow you to do more important things. By setting out a Strainer Base and installing a Strainer, you can get fish or some materials to use.

    Some Strainers require Bait, and you can dig up some Worms with a Garden Trowel for this! Get a Trowel, and I get you a Strainer as well.

Much of the hundreds of years of knowledge about Trains and Railroading was lost to the Cleansing. Proper track laying, large powerful engines, transporting a variety of things. We can regain this knowledge with Â§lÂ§nTRAINED IN UNLOCKÂ§r.

    The first, and simplest thing, we unlock is Â§6Â§lExtra RailsÂ§r, adding a couple helpful new minecart rails.

    Second is Â§6Â§lSteve's Carts 2 RebornÂ§r. Enabling you to create highly customizable, highly automatable mining carts should help net you all the resources you need to further The Plan.

    Last this book will unlock is Â§6Â§lImmersive RailroadingÂ§r. Recreate the trains of history, lay tracks down, expand the rail network.

You've regained the knowledge of how to craft fantastic trains, train tracks, and various other things with Immersive Railroading.

    You will need a lot of Steel and Treated Wood for this, so show me you have at least some stockpiled, as well as the Railroading Manual you'll need!

You've regained the knowledge of how to craft some specialized rails for Minecarts and other railbound transportation.

    Make some of the more mundane rails and I'll give you two of the specialized ones.

Automated Cart systems were a pretty big thing back in the days before the Cleansing. A smart Engineer can put together a few carts, and create an mini rail network that will grow trees and crops and harvest it all for them.

    Steve's Carts is one of these systems. The modularity of the carts will let you create a wide variety specialized creations, from simple transport to complex mining, smelting, and fabrication systems.

    Make the Cart Assembler, and I'll send you some Reinforced Metal to jumpstart your cart adventure.

A great variety of useful tools and machines came about under the Actually brand. They dipped their toes in many markets, and created a lot of useful gadgets for the populace. All these were lost in the Cleansing, but we can regain this knowledge with Â§lÂ§nACTUALLY UNLOCKÂ§r.

    The only thing you gain from reading this book is Â§6Â§lActually AdditionsÂ§r, but the wide range of tools it grants you is more than enough.

I'm not sure what else there is to say on Actually Additions. You can easily read their instruction manual, and in fact I'd like you to make it for me! 

    As well, please make the Coal Generator, as it will be useful for much more than Actually Additions creations. In return, I'll give you an Atomic Reconstructor, quite a neat little tool.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Big Things From A Small Book
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Many times, big things come in big packages. It's all about proportions. Factories, big drilling machines, and more. A lot of this knowledge was lost, but we can bring it back with Â§lÂ§nBIG MACHINE UNLOCKÂ§r.

    Reading this will unlocked two big things for you. Â§6Â§lImmersive EngineeringÂ§r adds a lot interesting machines and tools, like railguns, skyhooks, and more!

    The other knowledge you gain is Â§6Â§lEnvironmental TechÂ§r. Big multiblock machines are the cornerstone of this mod, from Solar Arrays to Void Miners.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Little Bit Punk, A Little Bit Diesel
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Some of our great machines weren't super high tech, fit in the palm gadgets, but big metal behemoths of wires, gears, and more. A little retro diesel and steam punk feeling, Immersive Engineering gives us a lot of great creations.

    An early thing you will need, for sure, is a Coke Oven, made of 27 Coke Bricks. Make those, and I'll give you the Hammer.

With the amount of people filling the cities before the Cleansing, more resources and more power were needed to fit the demand. Creations like Environmental Tech came about as an answer to the growing need.

    Environmental Tech has a handful of machines that expand out to multiblock creations. Each one has multiple tiers. Solar Arrays, Void Miners, Lightning Rods, and more.

    Make the first tier Solar Array Controller for me, and I'll give you an Assembler to help construct it with.

RF Energy has been the standard power for the world for many years, well before the Cleansing. Many companies, many product lines produced it and used it in various ways. Some of those lost can be regained by Â§lÂ§nRED GATE UNLOCKÂ§r.

    Â§6Â§lRFToolsÂ§r adds a variety of machines that can autocraft, store and sort items, and more. 

    Adding onto that is Â§6Â§lRFTools ControlÂ§r. It lets you program automation setups with RFTools and run them.

    Finally is Â§6Â§lProject RedÂ§r, providing Red Wire that you can run along walls and ceilings, and lots of logic gates and tools to control Redstone Signals.

RFTools (and RFTools Power) provides a variety of machines and tools that utilize RF Energy. From power generation to power storage, from automated crafters to storage trackers.

    Craft up a Coal Generator and I'll give you something to store the RF Energy in.

Expanding on RFTools, RFTools Control lets you design programs that lets you automate things. It connects with some RFTools items to work even better.

    Make a Programmer and I'll give you a small pile of Programmer Cards.

Redstone is the standard way to transmit signals to turn machines, lights, and more on or off. But Redstone is limited in that it can only lay on the floor. Complex creations like logic gates take up large amounts of room.

    Project Red helps fix this by providing various components and tools. Red Alloy Wire can be run along walls and ceilings. Logic Gates condense complex circuits down to the size of a few blocks. Other things such as lights, gems, and more are provided as well!

    The Screwdriver is quite helpful to rotate and configer logic gates. Make it and I'll give you quite a useful one!

Domesticating and training animals has been part of civilization since the forever, but the idea of more than simple taming was lost with the Cleansing. With Â§lÂ§nANIMAL STYLE UNLOCKÂ§r we can regain this knowledge.

    Â§6Â§lAnimaniaÂ§r adds a wide variety of animals, from ferrets to draft horses to hedgehogs!

    Though adding only a few creatures, Â§6Â§lAnimaliumÂ§r has a few interesting items you can use as well.

    The strange Â§6Â§lMeeCreepsÂ§r can do simple tasks for you, from chopping trees to mining. 

    Last but definitely not least is Â§6Â§lChocoCraftÂ§r. These large, feathered creatures can be tamed and bred to discover rarer types, ridden like horses, and are overall adorable.

A wide variety of animals inhabit the world, nature reclaiming parts of the landscape after the Cleansing. The monsters of the world tend to ignore regular animals and vice versa.

    Animania brings to the table a wide variety of animals, as well as some useful things like feed troughs, carts, and more!

    Why not make a trough for later, and I'll give you a cute hamster wheel for when you find one?

Dogs and Bears and Pirahnas, oh my. Animalium adds a few interesting creatures to the world.

    Show me some Bear Claws (not the pastry kind...) and I'll give you some Wild Dog Pelts.

Magical creatures have been seen across the world since the Cleansing. Large avians, as big as horses, and some intrepid survivors have taken to try taming and riding them.

    Gysahl Greens are the key to befriending them. Gather some and I'll give you a few nests for the creatures.

The magic from the Cleansing twisted in different ways. Some of it bad, some of it good, and some of it...weird. 

    MeeCreeps are little summonable... creatures... that will do small tasks for you. Make a Creep Cube and I'll give you a few Ender Pearls for another item from MeeCreeps.

Computer tech was very ingrained in everyday society. From the phones in our pockets to the very walls of our buildings, everything was infused with high technology. Even the digital age did not survive the Cleansing unscathed, but the lost knowledge can be redigitized with Â§lÂ§nDIGITALLY UNLOCKÂ§r.

    Â§6Â§lOpen ComputersÂ§r adds a set of programmable computers, drones, and more.

    As an add on to that, Â§6Â§lOpen PrinterÂ§r provides a working printer you can use in your Open Computer programs.

    Â§6Â§lOnline Picture FrameÂ§r allows you to display pictures from the Internet (or what's left of it!)

Computers help us do a lot of fantastic things, but for a majority of us how they work is a mystery. We don't know programming or microcircuit making, we just like it to work with little fuss.

    But for those of us who do know these things, Open Computers is excellent. With it, you can whip up programs to help with The Plan. 

    A Scrench is a very helpful tool with Open Computers (and many other technological devices!). Make it, and I'll give you the basic part for a Drone.

What is a computer system without a printer? Probably less frustrating...

    Open Printer adds a Printer that can connect to Open Computers and be accessed through programs.

    Here, make a Printer Paper Roll and I'll give you Color Ink. Even after the Cleansing its costly....

Digital picture frames were all the rage for... well, never. They saw minor popularity for a while, but ultimately were too fiddly compared to simple printed pictures and a picture frame.

    The Online Picture Frame is better, however. You can display a wall sized image in your home with very little work and no power requirement!

    Make one, and I'll give you a second one free!

With so much technology and machinery, the world needed strong power generators to meet the demand, as well as efficient ways to transmit it. The knowledge has corroded away with the Cleansing, but Â§lÂ§nPOWER UNLOCKEDÂ§r can bring it back.

    Â§6Â§lDeep ResonanceÂ§r takes the power of special crystals found deep underground and unleashes their energy potential.

    Not just for energy, Â§6Â§lXNetÂ§r brings a cable and router setup that can move power, items, and more around a powerful network.

With so many people filling the world, methods of coordinating the distribution of items, fluids, and power because a big business. One of the systems that was quite praised was XNet.

    XNet provides a network that you can set up to move around all the things above with a bit of work. Make a Controller, the basis of the XNet System, and I'll give you some cabling to get you started.

Before the Cleansing, researchers were just starting to look into a unique ore and crystals that seemed to resonate together in a unique way.

    Deep Resonance draws out the energy in these Resonating Crystals, providing ample amounts of power... if we can figure out how to tap into them properly.

    Process some of the Resonating Ore into Plates, and I'll give you one of these crystals.

Magic has always had a place in the world. Most of the time, magic and technology were used separately. Occasionally they were blended, but the vast differences between the two made it difficult, almost an art, to get them to play nice.  Â§lÂ§nCANTRIP : UNLOCKÂ§r recovers a few forms of magic lost to the Cleansing.

    Â§6Â§lEmbersÂ§r involves dwarven magic-tech, tapping into powerful resources below the Bedrock crust of the world.

    On the other hand, Â§6Â§lElectroblob's WizardryÂ§r is a solid, classic style of magical wizardry and casting.

Ember is a strange material that is found underneath the near-impenetrable Bedrock layer close to the Core of the world. The only technology that has been found to penetrate it correctly to harvest Ember is dwarven magi-tech.

    Embers, named after the powerful material, is the dwarven knowledge on how to find, harvest, and process Ember for a multitude of uses.

    Search the world for an Ancient Golem and destroy it, collecting the Ancient Core residing within. Do this, and I will give you a Tinker's Hammer, which you'll need for making metal plates.

Classic magic is a staple not only because its always been around, but because it is steeped in our fantasies as well.

    Electroblob's Wizardry is a classic example of magic. Wizard towers full of danger and magical spells, spellbooks and scrolls holding the keys to magic, wands to cast them, and even wizardly robes to wear!

    Make a basic Magic Wand and I'll give you some Crystal Ore to further your magical career!

The world is dangerous. Very dangerous. A lot of the offensive and defensive technology vanished with the Cleansing, but if we needed at any time, it is now. Â§lÂ§nARMED, ARMORED, AND UNLOCKEDÂ§r will get you re-equipped.

    Â§6Â§lMrCrayfish's Gun ModÂ§r gives you a bit of personal firepower with a variety of guns and scopes.

    To defend your base, Â§6Â§lOpen Modular TurretsÂ§r packs a defensive punch.

    Â§6Â§lSlashBladeÂ§r brings you powerful blades with the magic of combo power.

    Â§6Â§lTetraÂ§r brings modularity to some basic weapons and tools, unlocking their potential.

    If you don't want to fight in the first place, Â§6Â§lTorchmasterÂ§r helps stop monsters from appearing in the first place..

    Not just a child's weapon, Â§6Â§lYoyosÂ§r brings them to the battlefield with some new tricks.

Ancient blades of power were always a bit of a legend or fiction to most folks, but they did exist. They survived the Cleansing, but their existance and how to obtain their power became twisted instead. 

    SlashBlade is the name given to these dangerous weapons. They enable the wielder to slash and strike at hyper speed, dash into the air, and rack up the mystical Combo.

    The lesser blades became easily crafted, mere wood becoming a dangerous weapon. Craft the Anonimity-Wood sword, and I'll give you a BladeSoulIngot, the first step to the more deadly weapons.

Automated defenses weren't a big thing until technology advanced enough for reliable AI targetting. The technology was just taking a foothold when the Cleansing swept through, but now it is even more important with the dangers of the world.

    Open Modular Turrets give a variety of automated defensive turrets, their targetting configurable. You can make turrets recharge in daylight, fire faster, more accurately. 

    Make a Basic Turret Base Crank, which lets you generate RF Energy by hand, and I'll give you a Tier 1 Turret Base to install it into.

MrCrayfish covered a wide line of products before the Cleansing. One of the lesser known ones was this line of weaponry.

    MrCrayfish's Gun Mod brings a simple line of firearms with the ability to attach scopes to each of them.

    Make a Pistol and I'll give you a scope for it.

At one point in history, Yoyos were a weapon. Possibly. Maybe. Okay, it's mostly a legend and myth and has no real historical basis.

    But since the Cleansing, this children's toy has taken to the legends and become a weapon. See for yourself, make an Iron Yoyo and I'll give you an Enchanted Book to make your Yoyo a bit more fun.

After the Cleansing, some mundane products and creations were imbued with magic. Torchmaster items were such, simply lighting areas to keep creatures and pests away.

    Now the torches and lights Torchmaster provides can keep monsters and creatures from even appearing from the magical void. They also can magically dispense lights in an area for you.

    Make their flagship product the Mega Torch and I'll toss you a Terrain Lighter.

Usually, once you've made a weapon or tool, that's it. You can enchant it, maybe repair it, maybe turn it into a new weapon. But what if you had the ability to change certain pieces of it?

    Replace the handle with a stronger one. Refine the blade. Balance it better. Tetra lets you do this. 

    You'll need a Log Hammer to get the upgraded Crafting Bench. You can then use this Geode in the bench!

No matter who you are, as long as you are alive, you gotta eat. Simple foods fill the belly, but don't quite fill the soul, right? Generations of cooking knowledge was spoiled by the Cleansing, but Â§lÂ§nAN EDIBLE UNLOCKÂ§r will get the kitchen heating up once again.

    Â§6Â§lTaco TuesdayÂ§r is good for any day of the week. Who doesn't like Tacos? Savory and sweet versions included!

    Hemp just isn't for making rope and twine. Â§6Â§lImmersive HempcraftÂ§r covers the recreational and medicinal sides of cultivating Hemp.

    With so many new things to cook and ingredients to collect, Â§6Â§lCooking for BlockheadsÂ§r and its multiblock kitchen should make things much easier.

    And lastly, many recipes require fruits from large trees. If space is an issue, Â§6Â§lBonsai TreesÂ§r adds miniature growing pots to help.

Somewhat misunderstood, Hemp and Hemp products had steadily began to come back into regular use in society... at least before the Cleansing. Since then, hemp has seen a definite resurgance in popularity.

    Immersive Hempcraft expands on Immersive Engineering's Industrial Hemp, creating a crop that has industrial, commercial, and recreational use.

    Mix up some Basic Potting Soil for your crops, and I'll give you some Apetite, which will help you in cultivating better products.

Delicious tacos. Crunch or soft. Savory or sweet. Who can say no?

    Taco Tuesday adds a menu full of different kinds of tacos, some of them imparting magical buffs when eaten.

    Make a couple basic Crunchy Beef Tacos, and I'll give you a special Taco Taco! It's a taco that is packed full of taco goodness.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Variety is the Spice of Life
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
So many different plants and animals cover this world, especially after the Cleansing. Nature has taken back over in many places, and this gives us a big opportunity to explore new culinary horizons.

    Pam's Harvestcraft brings many ingredients, many dishes to the table. Lots of new crops to grow and things to eat. It also adds a few new machines and ways to gather ingredients.

    Make half a dozen basic Donuts and I'll give you one of my favorite fruits, in the form of a Mango Tree Sapling.

There are so many tasty, fantastic recipes around the world, that keeping track of them with a simple recipe book is daunting. Especially when magic is afoot.

    Cooking for Blockheads provides an expandable multiblock kitchen that can examine your inventory and its kitchen cabinets full of ingredients and utensils, and tell you exactly what you can make on the spot.

    Make the Cooking Table, the core of your new kitchen, and I'll throw in an Oven for you.

Large orchards can be a hassle to tend, especially with all the dangerous monsters lurking about. Flattening all the land in the first place, especially, is a chore.

    Bonsai Trees gives you two simple plant pots that you can grow miniature versions of most any tree, and harvest materials from them once fully grown. 

    Make the regular Bonsai Pot and I'll give you a Hopping version.

Even before the Cleansing, magic infused much of the world. It's use fell out of favor to technology, but practitioners could be found here and there. Now, those versed in the magic arts are much much harder to find, and all the knowledge even more difficult to gather. With Â§lÂ§nDARK MAGICIAN UNLOCKÂ§r will get you re-equipped.

    Â§6Â§lBaublesÂ§r supplies us with a variety of new places to wear accessories, like the Mining Ring.

    Â§6Â§lBotaniaÂ§r harnesses the magical power of flowers in a almost technological way.

    Â§6Â§lPSIÂ§r gives you the power to program custom magical spells and cast them by firing a gun.

Magic and Technology don't tend to get along well together. Rarely, though, they blend into something new and unique.

    Botania can best be described as such. Some magic blended into a fairly technological creation at its core. Utilizing the power of Flowers to generate and consume Mana, which then creates various materials, tools, and more.

    Create a pile of Manasteel Ingots to get yourself started, and I'll give you a Mana Diamond to boost you forward.

At one point in history, Yoyos were a weapon. Possibly. Maybe. Okay, it's mostly a legend and myth and has no real historical basis.

    But since the Cleansing, this children's toy has taken to the legends and become a weapon. See for yourself, make an Iron Yoyo and I'll give you an Enchanted Book to make your Yoyo a bit more fun.

Accessories have always been a thing for both fashion and function. A pretty necklace, a shiny gold ring. A key that's actually a knife and screwdriver. A hat with built in headphones.

    Baubles does not have much to its own, but instead expands multiple other things, especially magic mods. What is a wizard without a bunch of magical rings, a cape, a pointy hat....

    How about making a Fancy Ring and I'll give you a Diamond.

Magic is all about balance. Light and dark, good and evil, give and take. Take too much and the world will overbalance. Taint is the corruption that occurs when this happens with some magic. 

    Thaumcraft is the school of magic that deals with tapping into the magic of the world to rebalance it. Breaking down everyday objects into their magical components and recombining them into tools to aid you.

    Create a decent amount of Salis Mundus, and I'll give you a Silverwood Sapling, with its purity able to fight off the Taint.

We are a fairly materialistic society, especially since the Cleansing. We keep and hoard items, partially to survive, but also to keep hold of parts of the world close. Many storage solutions, however, were lost to the ages, at least until Â§lÂ§nA PLACE FOR UNLOCKSÂ§r unboxes the knowledge.

    Â§6Â§lIron ChestsÂ§r has upgradeable chests to help organize things.

    Â§6Â§lIron BackpacksÂ§r is perfect for on the go. Upgradeable backpacks to make every journey away from home worthwhile.

    If fields of chests aren't your thing, Â§6Â§lStorage DrawersÂ§r adds more elegant looking solutions. Yes, they as well are upgradeable.

    If you want something higher tech, Â§6Â§lRefined StorageÂ§r is exactly what you want. Digitize and store your collection in a network!

    Not enough? Â§6Â§lReborn StorageÂ§r adds a multiblock crafter to Refined Storage.

    And finally, Â§6Â§lRefined Storage AddonsÂ§r adds a few final tools to the Refined Storage mix.

Chests and boxes are all well and good for storage, but it lacks a certain style. They are more difficult to organize and keep track of how many of an item you have, for example.

    Storage Drawers may take up more room, but it looks much more elegant. Each Drawer can have up to 4 smaller drawers, and visibly shows the item in each once!

    Make a Drawer Key, which lets you lock the kind of item the drawer can hold, and I'll give you an Iron Upgrade, which increases its capacity!

There aren't a lot of solutions for those on the go. Our pockets are magically bigger by default (not even the Cleansing changed that), but it never seems to be enough!

    Iron Backpacks gives us that much needed extra inventory space when we're away from home. Every trip into the dangerous world is important, so carrying everything you can get to ensure survival is paramount.

    Make a Basic Backpack and I'll give you an Upgrade for it that'll show you how full it is without having to open it.

Refined Storage's reclaimation brought with it a few additional tools.

    Refined Storage Addons only adds a few specialized tools, but they can be quite helpful in the right setup.

    Make a Wireless Crafting Grid and I'll get you a Network Picker to go with it.

Refined Storage is based on an older technology that has since been lost to the Cleansing. We haven't been able to resurrect the entire tech, but a piece of it came back along with Refined Storage.

    Reborn Storage adds a multiblock pattern crafter. By combining Crafting CPUs and storage blocks, you can add an alternate high speed autocrafter to your Refined Storage system.

    Make one of the Crafting CPUs and I'll give you a handful of Crafting Frames for your machine.

Technology had advanced by leaps and bounds in the years before the Cleansing, and the inventors and researchers of Ferretopia and Port Burda have been furthering what they can. Without key research, though, progress was slow.

    With some of that knowledge recovered, Refined Storage is now a possibility. You can create a computer network that can digitize and store items by the hundreds in a small footprint. 

    The core of this system is the Controller. Make it, and I'll give you another key component, the Solderer.

Wooden chests tucked into corners has been one of the standard storage themes for the survivors of the Cleansing. If it works, it works, but there should be more elegant solutions.

    Iron Chests fits that, I feel. Upgrade your mundane looking chests to stronger, better metal ones! All without having to empty and pick up the chest.

    Make an Iron Chest and I'll give you an Iron to Gold Chest Upgrade.

Factgory automation was a growing practice in the world. More efficient and less costly, it was steadily sought by many big companies. Much of these machines and practices were lost in the Cleansing, but Â§lÂ§nFACTORY UNLOCKÂ§r brings some of it back for you.

    Â§6Â§lIndustrial ForegoingÂ§r provides a plethora of machines that automate crop, animal, monster, and item farming, along with crafting and many other things.

    Not exactly automation based, but fitting in many catagories at once, Â§6Â§lCyclicÂ§r brings a great variety of machines, items, and more that you can use in many situations.

Being able to automate small things gives one time to focus on the bigger things. So automating bigger things should give even more time.

    Industrial Foregoing gives you plenty of machines that, when put together smartly, automate a lot bigger tasks, giving you time to enjoy (and survive) life.

    For example, you can make an Animal Feeder to automatically feed and breed your animals. Do that, and you can take this Resource Fisher, which automatically fishes for you.

Sometimes, you can't place something into a single catagory or genre. They spread out so much, they touch a bit of everything.

    Cyclic is much like that. It has items to help you adventure, to protect your base, to create new items, and more.

    An example is these Climbing Gloves you can make, which turn walls into ladders for you. Make them, and you can have this Ender Wing Prime, which will teleport you back to the last bed you slept in.

Never underestimate form and decor when it comes to living post-Cleansing. There is a difference between merely surviving and actually living. Good food, good atmosphere, good homes. Much of the magic of decor and furniture vanished, but Â§lÂ§nTHE DESIGNER UNLOCKÂ§r should bring an entire furniture store to your fingertips.

    Â§6Â§lStatuesÂ§r are a great way to adorn entrances to your grand halls.

    Unique looking structures stand out, and Â§6Â§lXTonesÂ§r brings brings a lot of variety to your building materials.

    Â§6Â§lBibliocraftÂ§r provides all the furniture you could need to make a nice looking AND functional house!

    Just filling your house with furniture isn't enough. Â§6Â§lDecocraftÂ§r can help bring together a themed room or just add all the little details that make a house a home.

    Â§6Â§lMrCrayfish's Furniture ModÂ§r adds a lot of nice things for around the house, the garden, and more.

    Need your buildings themselves to have a lot more texture and style to them? Â§6Â§lChisels and BitsÂ§r lets you break down blocks into tiny pieces, and build them back up in all three dimensions!

A lot of structures have a certain look. Many times its just what materials were available. Other times, great care is taken in the visual texture of a building.

    XTones adds to your building repretoire in interesting ways. The blocks can easily be shifted to a handful of different variations, which makes getting just the right look easier.

    It even provides a lighting option. Make a Flat Lamp for me and I'll pass along some Zyth blocks, which look neat.

Ever wish you could just take a little piece of one material and add it to another? Like laying tiles to create a mosaic, but in all three dimensions?

    Chisels and Bits lets you break apart whole blocks of material, and put them back together piece by piece. Give a creation some depth with actual holes, furrows, and raised sections.

    Make a Diamond Bit Saw to cut the blocks down, and I'll give you a Chiseled Bit Bag to hold the pieces.

betterquesting:10.name:8: A Good Book and a Nice Chair
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
A comfortable chair, a library of books, just enough light to read by. Sometimes its good to get away from the grind of survival and just sit back and relax. 

    Bibliocraft gives you plenty of options for furniture, not only for a home either. Castles, militaristic bases, you can find something that fits well, especially with the customizable Framed furniture!

    How about this. Craft up a Purple Typewriter and I'll give you a Grandfather Clock for your wall.

Just as much as the wallpaper color, furniture, and carpet design help tell you what a room is for, the little things are what can fully sell it. A dark grey room with iron bars may be a jail, may be an animal pen, or might just be an abandoned boiler room. 
 
    But if you add a chained up skeleton prop it becomes a dungeon. Stack up a bunch of barrels and instead you have a brewery storage room!

    Decocraft gives you hundreds of items that can make your rooms pop! And it all starts with the Decobench. Craft that up and I'll give you this cute little Music Box for your room.

MrCrayfish has a lot of different product lines, but the most popular one is MrCrayfish's Furniture Mod. A little bit of everything for the home, from chairs and tables to grills and coolers.

    Get yourself a nice TV and I'll give you a Trampoline for your yard.

Statues are a great way to decorate. Statue gardens can show off great works, each one memorializing a significant event, creature, person, or object.

    They don't have to even memorialize something grand. Statues of a group of friends could be a good talking piece. Or a statue of a monster, complete with sounds, could be used for Halloween. 

    There's an idea. Make a Decorative Zombie Statue for when the spooky times roll around, and I'll give you this weird Decorative Shulker Statue.

Sometimes you don't know you miss something until its gone. A liked food, an enjoyed game, a fun toy, a useful but obscure tool. Little gadgets and gizmos can be quite useful or just plain fun. The Cleansing took much of these away, but  Â§lÂ§nGOGO GADGET UNLOCKÂ§r will pull them back out of the top hat once more.

    Need to test a new weapon? Â§NÂ§lÂ§6Â§lMmmMmmMmmMmmÂ§r might be a strange name for a product line, but provides a super useful testing dummy.

    Found a bunch of junk amongst the treasure when exploring the Lost Cities? Â§6Â§lCorail RecyclerÂ§r will let you dissassemble them to get the more useful materials out of them.

    Â§6Â§lMrCrayfish's Jumping Castle ModÂ§r returns your childhood antics with giant bouncing castles of your own design!

    Lastly and most usefully, Â§6Â§lNot Enough WandsÂ§r brings magical abilities to the mundane world.

Did you ever see as a kid those brightly colored, giant inflatable castles? Kids would jump into them and bounce all around, knocking into each other and having a ball.

    Now you can make your own giant inflatable castle. Or how about a mansion? What about a bouncy mall? MrCrayfish's Jumping Castle Mod brings you all this joy!

    Make five of the White Castle Blocks and I'll give you five Purple Castle Blocks.

Traveling to other worlds was a rare thing before the Cleansing, but it happened. I don't mean space travel, but rather other dimensions. Not only that, we had more forms of travel than horses, minecarts, and our own two feet. Unfortunately, the skies became lost to us, but we can reclaim them with Â§lÂ§nA DISTANT UNLOCKÂ§r.

    Starting small, Â§6Â§lElevatorsÂ§r help you get around your larger bases with ease.

    Retake the skies with Â§6Â§lViescraftÂ§r, zeppelins and dirigables back in your control.

    Other dimensions are once again open to you, such as the Â§6Â§lHunting DimensionÂ§r, a dangerous world to test your battle prowess.

    Lastly, another dimension will let you gather resources without destroying our own dimension. Â§6Â§lAroma1997's Dimensional WorldÂ§r is much like home, only empty.

The dragons have returned. Not the regular ones in Ferretopia and Port Burda, I mean the giant, ancient ones that vanished long ago. The Cleansing broke the seal that kept them out, and now they are back...kind of. They cannot reach the Overworld, but the mysterious End is another matter. But with their return, is the power to fight them back as well? Â§lÂ§nBLUE EYES WHITE UNLOCKÂ§r is the key to this millenium old puzzle.

    Â§6Â§lDraconic EvolutionÂ§r is the path to fighting the dragons... with their own power. Take the fight to them.

A lot of this world is filled with leftover junk from when civilization thrived. Some of it is nothing more than crumbled and deteriorated, while other pieces are quite useful to you. And in between is the useful junk. Things that still work, but you have no use for.

    You could just leave them there, and maybe someone else will find them, or maybe they'll just break down themselves. You could bring it with you, but that quickly fills your adventuring bags, and you may never find a use for it.

    Or you could break it down with Corail Recycler. This machine isn't able to break down everything, but a lot of junk you find in the Lost Cities should be fair game.

    Make one of the Recyclers and I'll give you a Diamond disk, which the Recycler requires to work.

betterquesting:10.name:8: This is Where You Fall Down
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
In this dangerous world, its always important to have a good weapon to defend yourself with. But with so many options, it may be difficult to tell what is a really good weapon without diving headfirst into a knife fight with a pack of zombies.

    MmmMmmMmmMmm, before the Cleansing, produced only one item : The Test Dummy. It was widely popular as both a training tool and a test of ability. It calculated your "Damage Per Second" as you attacked it. Quite useful, right?

    Make one and I'll give you a second one free!

Wands have always been one of the big symbols of a wizard. A flick, a swish, and sparkles happen and suddenly the drunk customer is an iguana for a few minutes.

    Not Enough Wands brings the magic to the mundane. These simple wands do one kind of task each, and are useful in various ways.

    For example! Craft yourself a Building Wand, great for quickly building structures. As a reward, you'll get my Swapping Wand, great for upgrading a structure's materials, or building with cheap blocks and replacing them later.

Stairs are a great invention. They go up, they go down, you get exercise... but sometimes you want to be lazy. or 20 flights of stairs are just not feasible after running across the desert with three packs full of goodies.

    The OpenBlocks Elevator is simple to use. Just install them in a column, then Jump or Crouch to teleport between Elevators! Handy!

    They only work in pairs, so make me a pair of White Elevators, and I'll give you a pair of Purple Elevators.

Helicopters, jets, airplanes. All things that broke down and disappeared with the Cleansing. There aren't giant factories producing and maintining them anymore, so it is no surprise. But the skies are something we are always reaching for.

    Viescraft enables us to reclaim the skies using zeppelins and dirigibles! They are customizable as well!

    Start building a ship, getting an Airship Balloon ready, and I'll give up a Balloon Upgrade.

The twisted magic of the Cleansing touched more than our dimension. The Nether and The End are two examples of places we gained much easier access to, for example. The Dimensional World, however, is new.

    We've found the Aroma1997's Dimensional World (named for the first discoverer of course!) is an alternate dimension that is almost perfectly... flat. And it is always daytime. The world seems untouched, a great source of materials to pull back home.

    The endless daytime and flat world seems to be quite... unsettling to many folks. The dimension appears to be missing some key things, so it is not suggested to make a home there.

    Make some of the Portal Frames you'll need for the doorway to this strange world. I'll give you the Multitool you'll need to summon the portal itself.

Since the Cleansing, our world has become quite dangerous. Magic twisted and created monsters that roam the land. It also created another dimension. A dimension full of darkness, where you are likely to be eaten by a grue. Well, not a grue, but swarms of monsters.

    This may seem like a bad thing, but some monsters are the only way to get rare materials, and with so many in the Overworld, it might be tough to find the specific one.

    Make some Hunting Dimension Frame in Oak Wood, and I will share some Creeping Moss with you, of the Hell Variety. This'll let you transform a small bit of land in the Hunting Dimension to Hell.

Dragons, ancient ones that returned after the Cleansing, are deadly beasts. They can rip through the terrain as well as the flesh from your bones. Their home, The End, has been built up to aid them by the Endermen, magic crystals healing and protecting them.

    And with Draconic Evolution, you can harness all this power for yourself, and fight them toe to toe. 

    Your key to learning this is the Draconic Evolution Information Tablet. Make it, learn from it, and I'll give you some Draconium to help you in your fight.

Insanity. That sums it up. The Cleansing, I have to say, has shattered the limits of reality. Researchers in Ferretopia and Port Burda all agree : there is a level of power that can be obtained that is near Infinity. It is dangerous, and crazy, but if you are willing... we will provide Â§lÂ§nTHE RIDONKULOUS UNLOCKÂ§r if you show us your dedication.

    Â§6Â§lAvaritiaÂ§r is what we call this path. With it you can obtain the power of the Cosmos itself

    Â§6Â§lAvaritia TweaksÂ§r are some new things we've researched and discovered. Curiosity may be the end of us, but what a way to go.

When you break the veil of reality, you never know what you'll find. Just Avaritia is not enough, it seems, as the twisting cosmos have more tricks up their sleeves.

    Avaritia Tweaks returns some lost items to reality. Things forgotten even before the Cleansing.

    Make an Enhancement Crystal, which will further break the cosmos in two for you, and a Gaia Block is yours.

What can I say about this? This path lies madness, insanity...but also determination.

    Avaritia will take so much of your knowledge, power, and resources to delve into. Thousands and thousands and thousands of resources are required. All this to pierce the final veils of reality and obtain some form of Nirvana.

   If you succeed in this power, go punch the Ancient Ones for us, okay? Until then, make one Crystal Matrix Ingot, and I'll give you a second one.
Building the rail network of The Plan is going to take a lot of metal. Train tracks, trains, rail stations, all of it is very dependant on metal supplies.

While Ferretopia and Port Burda can use some of the supplies asked here, the bigger benefit can be had by those surviving in villages scattered among the Lost Cities. 

    The logistics of receiving, storing, then delivering so many different goods is something we can handle, but it takes time, money, and resources.

    Just note that the requests here will much less favorable to you than if you traded the items directly to those who need them.

    Â§o[The quests here for Purple Rail Tickets and Gold Rail Tickets can be 10x more expensive(or higher!) than finding Quest or Trader NPCs in villages or in the wilderness.]

Â§lREQUESTÂ§r : 100 Iron Ingots
    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :  50 Dollars
                     2 Purple Rail Ticket

The Plan will burn through thousands of basic materials. Wood, stone, etc.

We have some Yellow Rail Tickets we can sell you, but they will cost a whole lot more than a villager can offer.
    Â§o[This amount will go up when more CustomNPCs are added]

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :   20 Dollars
                      2 Purple Rail Ticket

Ferretopia and Port Burda have very efficient farms, but we have focused on quick growing, highly nutritious crops. We have some variety, but the outside world has all sorts of flavors and ingredients.

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :   30 Dollars
                      2 Purple Rail Ticket

We have some special requests from the Ferretopia and Port Burda leaders.

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :   75 Dollars
                      2 Purple Rail Ticket

A good Smeltery and some carefully hand-crafted tools. Nothing says do-it-yourself more than that! Tinker's Construct brings all this together with so many options its dizzying.

    Make half a stack of Seared Bricks, you'll need them. I'll give you the Smeltery Controller to help you along..

It's one thing to get some solid metal armor to protect yourself, but many times it doesn't look great. Or you have all sorts of different pieces, and none of it matches! Cosmetic Armor lets you wear TWO sets of armor! You'll look like one set, and use the other set for protection! The best of both worlds!

    Get an Iron Chestplate and I'll add a pair of Iron Leggings to your outfit.

Better Questing does not automatically update the quest book when a modpack updates.

    If the pack recently updated, please complete this quest. It will reset itself after a long cooldown so that it is harder to abuse in servers.

Statues require a Statue Core to make them, which mostly only come from Statue Bats (they have begun appearing in Loot Bags recently, according to reports...). 
 
    If you are having minimal luck in finding Statue Bats in caverns and loot bags, you can purchase some from us.

Chocobo seem to live in odd conditions unless tamed and raised by someone. Your part of the world may lack them for various reasons.

    We've got a few chocobo farms going, providing travel mounts for various merchants. We can sell some basic Chocobo eggs to you from one of these farms.

Magic, technology, they have issues working together sometimes. But take a programmer's approach to magic and you can create wonders all on your own!

    PSI lets you program spells piece by piece, using mathmatical concepts and formula, to create a wide variety of effects. You then imprint these spells onto Spell Bullets, and cast them from your CAD Assembly, a powerful spellcasting gun!

    It even has a built in guide for you that is easy to access, and helps you from step one!

    Make a Spell Programmer, and I'll give you a Basic CAD Core for your first CAD Assembly!

Â§lREQUESTÂ§r :    20 of each pie specified
    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :   100 Dollars
                       2 Purple Rail Ticket
Creatures and Monsters have various supplies we can research and use.

Â§lREQUESTÂ§r :  50 Bones
                    10 Necrotic/Withered Bones
    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :  30 Dollars
                     2 Purple Rail Ticket

Â§lREQUESTÂ§r :  10 Skeleton Skulls
                    10 Zombie Heads
                     5 Creeper Heads
                     5 Wither Skulls
    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :  80 Dollars
                     2 Purple Rail Ticket

    Â§l   NOTES Â§r:  Â§rÂ§oBeheading enchantments/abilities are required for some heads.

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :    20 Dollars
                       2 Purple Rail Ticket

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :   75 Dollars
                      2 Purple Rail Ticket

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :    50 Dollars
                       2 Purple Rail Ticket

    Â§lREWARDSÂ§r :    50 Dollars
                       2 Purple Rail Ticket

Certain survivors of the Cleansing had bits and pieces of the Knowledge that was lost. One of them is the Machinist, who holds the blueprints for two pieces of Immersive Engineering that are quite hard to replicate. 

    We've brought some of these Machinists back home, and they are offering copies of the blueprints for a price.

    You could try finding another Machinist in a village, but they are quite difficult to find due to the hostile conditions.

Hello? Is this thing on?
    Â§o[It's transmitting, Sir. Adjusting... They can hear you now.]Â§r
    Good, thank you Bitsy. Ahem...
    Hello there! My name is Caigan. I'm the owner of The Ferret Business. We've come across your dimensional signal as we have been searching for... well, an important employee of ours, to make it simple. We're trying to rescue them from a bit of a sticky dimensional trap they've gotten into.
    Alas, we've not found any good leads yet. But we have found multiple new business opportunities, including FOGCraft and Port Burda! We've begun discussions with The Conductor on how we can help each other, and they have allowed us to contact all of you Engineers via this Ledger.
    Unfortunately, your world's run in with the Elder Gods has warped the dimensional and magical fabric and... uh... Well, I'd rather not get into the technicalities, we'll be here for days. But what it means is we're fairly limited in what we can offer each other.
    We can only send certain items back and forth, so I propose a trade offer. You have multiple metals and resources we are quite interested in, and there are some things we should be able to send you in return.

All stories begin somewhere, and this is where yours starts. Learn how you got here and where you are going. And more importantly, how...

While much of the knowledge of the world was lost, Ferretopia was able to save some of the knowledge, as well as develop our own. I can give you the very basics of what we know, you'll have to research further on your own...
    I'll also give you some quickstart manuals on each of these that might be helpful

The Ancient Ones devoured the much of the knowledge in their Cleansing of the world. But knowledge and power are never destroyed, just merely misplaced and forgotten.
    Using the magic of the Rail Tickets, Ferretopia and Port Burda scientists can bring back the lost thoughts as Knowledge Books.

Ferretopia and Port Burda survived the Cleansing because they weren't big cities. Their small size made them easy to protect. But with The Plan underway, we're going to need a lot of supplies. 
    We'll add more things we need over time as we need them.
With multiple Engineers across the world, and merchants and traders spreading out as well, Ferretopia and Port Burda have access to some resources that may be hard to come by in your area.

As we uncover knowledge lost by the Cleansing, we discover even more mysteries lost simply to time and space.

    And then we also learn new things, and find new allies in strange places.
